<div id="stitle" style="display:none;">Notebook Entry</div>
<dl id="n12135c"> <dt class="nbunit"><a name="n12" href="#n12135c">N12 (VI.B.14)</a>:  <a href="../../ff/fnbs/n12all.htm#n12135c"> 135(c)</a></dt> <dd> <blockquote> Caucas. foetus = Negro / &mdash; infant = mongol</blockquote> <dd class="well"> <blockquote class="sources"><font color="green">[About Robert Chambers and his proto-Darwinian work from 1844, <cite>Vestiges of the Natural History of Creation</i>]</font>: Anticipating the doctrine now known as that of recapitulation by the individual of the history of the race, he maintained that <mark>a Caucasian foetus represents the Negro stage, and a Caucasian infant the Mongol stage, of human evolution</mark>. <small> F.G. Crookshank, <a name="MIOM" href="../../ff/fdra/fdex.htm#MIOM"><cite title="source">The Mongol in Our Midst</cite></a> (1924) 9</small></blockquote> </dd></dl>
